      <title>Re: Need for external table to store multiple_o...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/integrate/forum/general/need_for_external_table_to_store_multiple_option_values/re_need_for_external_table_to_store_multiple_o2</link>
      <description>Indeed, reverse lookups are interesting.&#13;
The obvious advantage of having the multiple choice inline is not having to setup extra tables - both can coexist, as you have proposed.&#13;
&#13;
Rather than adding an option to the multiple choice for external-table-or-not, I'd do what the standard selection type does, ie. add an option to the single-external-table type to make it either single or multiple choice. But I leave the final decision up to you.&#13;
&#13;
One other datatype I've been developing is a 'linked selection' datatype, which uses the options from another, existing class attribute. I think it might also be a nice addition...</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Gaetano Giunta)</author>
