      <description>Hi Gaetano&#13;
&#13;
The sites where I've used it have utilised the external table to provide forward and reverse lookups of the connected data and associated content objects.  I find it's much easier to do when the values are stored in the DB. &#13;
&#13;
The externalMultipleOptionSearch extended attribute filter replies on this.&#13;
&#13;
Do you have some use cases where storing the values in the data_text format is ideal?  I think it would be fine for simply storing and presenting the data but would add extra processing.&#13;
&#13;
What are your thoughts on adding an option to the datatype to allow the user to choose between the two (external table/data_text) ?&#13;
&#13;
Cheers&#13;
Bruce</description>
