    <item>
      <title>Re: Concrete example</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/integrate/forum/general/concrete_example/re_concrete_example</link>
      <description>Hi Stéphane&#13;
&#13;
I've built  many projects that integrated existing database content with eZ content objects.  In most cases datatypes were the easiest way to do this and I noticed that they were all quite similar so built the extension as a generic solution.&#13;
&#13;
On the Melink Melbourne (public transport for Victoria, Australia) site it is used to link service alterations with transport routes:&#13;
http://www.metlinkmelbourne.com.au/news/service_alterations/metropolitan_trains/extra_trains_for_australia_v_sri_lanka_one_day_international_cricket_match_friday_29_february_2008&#13;
&#13;
The Affected lines are a Multiple option that links a service alteration eZ content object to the Lines table in existing public transport database.&#13;
&#13;
The service updates can then be linked to both eZ content as well as custom content like timetables:&#13;
http://www.metlinkmelbourne.com.au/line/view/35#serviceUpdates&#13;
&#13;
The datatypes can also be used in place of the existing selection attributes.  They are especially handy if you have a long list of items or the same list is used across multiple content classes.  &#13;
I've used them for country lists prior to the recently included country dataype.&#13;
&#13;
Cheers&#13;
Bruce</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Bruce Morrison)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/integrate/forum/general/concrete_example/re_concrete_example</guid>
